      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Hypermobility MD / Bendy Bodies, LLC ("we," "us," or "our") respects your privacy. This policy explains what information we collect through this website and how we use it.</p>

      <h2>Information We Collect Through Forms</h2>
      <p>When you submit a form on this site (such as the contact form, booking form, podcast question form, or guest information form), we collect the information you provide. This may include your name, email address, phone number, and the content of your message or responses.</p>
      <p>Form submissions are sent to a private Google Sheet accessible only to authorized members of the Hypermobility MD team. Your information is used solely for the purpose described on each form and is never sold or shared with third parties.</p>

      <h2>Google reCAPTCHA</h2>
      <p>This site uses Google reCAPTCHA v3 to protect forms from spam and abuse. reCAPTCHA collects hardware and software information (such as device and application data) and sends it to Google for analysis. Your use of reCAPTCHA is subject to Google's <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="https://policies.google.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Terms of Service</a>.</p>

      <h2>Google Analytics</h2>
      <p>We use Google Analytics to understand how visitors use our site, including which pages are viewed and how users navigate between them. Google Analytics collects anonymized usage data through cookies.</p>
      <p><strong>Important:</strong> For HIPAA compliance, Google Analytics does <strong>not</strong> track activity on any form pages, and we do not record or track links to form pages. This means your visits to our contact, booking, podcast question, and guest information forms are not tracked by analytics.</p>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>This site uses cookies for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics cookies</strong> (<code>_ga</code>, <code>_gid</code>) — used to distinguish unique visitors and track site usage. These cookies are not set on form pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Google reCAPTCHA cookies</strong> — used to verify that form submissions come from real people, not bots.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use cookies for advertising, retargeting, or any purpose beyond the above.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>Our site contains links to third-party websites (e.g., product affiliates, podcast platforms, social media). We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites. We encourage you to review their privacy policies.</p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>This site is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 without parental consent. Our booking form requires confirmation that the submitter is 13 or older, and our podcast question form requires confirmation that the submitter is 18 or older.</p>

      <h2>Data Security</h2>
      <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the information you submit through our forms. All form submissions are transmitted over HTTPS and stored in access-controlled systems. However, no method of internet transmission is 100% secure.</p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of any personal information you have submitted through our forms by contacting us at <a href="/contact/">our contact page</a>.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on this page with an updated "Last updated" date.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.</p>

